						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> infront of the central shrine, of the Vṛiddhagirīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 15: 986 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records that Paravēḷūr Pērarasaṉ Koṇḍa-nāḍu-uḍaiyāṉ Kuṉṟan donated ten <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for burning a perpetual lamp to the god, Tirumudukuṉṟam uḍaiyār. The <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Arikulakēsari-chaturvēdimaṅgalam received the gold and agreed to measure out an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee daily.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX. No. 374.</p>						

						</summary>
